if you’ve never worked before, you might not know that taxes are withheld on each and every dollar that you make. if you live and work in california, you will see deductions for federal tax withholding, social security, medicare, state disability insurance, and a withholding for state taxes. depending on the state or the city you live in, you may see other deductions. for more detailed description of these items specifically related to california, refer to the california tax service center website. email: fao@sjsu.edu _________________________ phone: 408-283-7500 ext 4 monday to friday 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. _________________________ live chat tuesday to friday 12:00 p.m. to 4:00 p.m. __________________________ virtual appointments friday from 10:00 a.m - 3:00 p.m. _________________________ in-person appointments monday to thursday 8:15 a.m. to 4:45 p.m. friday 9:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. __________________________ student services center (ssc) 9 street & san fernando (on 1 floor of north parking garage) financial aid and scholarship office san josé state university one washington square san jose, ca 95192-0036 